By default, JupyterLab‚Äôs `IFrame` widget does **not** set an explicit `referrerpolicy`, meaning the browser may send the full referrer depending on its default behavior. To control this, you can explicitly set the `referrerpolicy` attribute on the `<iframe>`.

### Recommended Options for `referrerpolicy`
- **`no-referrer`** ‚Üí Completely hides the referrer.
- **`no-referrer-when-downgrade`** ‚Üí Sends referrer only over HTTPS.
- **`origin`** ‚Üí Sends only the origin (e.g., `https://your-jupyterlab.com`).
- **`strict-origin-when-cross-origin`** *(Default in modern browsers)* ‚Üí Sends full referrer on same-origin but only the origin on cross-origin requests.

### How to Set `referrerpolicy` in JupyterLab
If you are using the `IFrame` widget from `@jupyterlab/ui-components`, you can modify its underlying DOM element:

```typescript
import { IFrame } from '@jupyterlab/ui-components';
import { Widget } from '@lumino/widgets';

// Create an IFrame widget
const iframe = new IFrame();
iframe.url = 'https://your-trusted-origin.com';
iframe.node.style.width = '100%';
iframe.node.style.height = '100vh';

// Remove sandbox and set referrer policy
iframe.node.removeAttribute('sandbox');
iframe.node.setAttribute('referrerpolicy', 'no-referrer'); // Adjust as needed

// Wrap in a widget and add to layout
const panel = new Widget();
panel.node.appendChild(iframe.node);
```

### Alternative: Plain `<iframe>` for More Control
If you bypass the `IFrame` widget and use a raw `<iframe>`, you can directly control the attributes:

```typescript
import { Widget } from '@lumino/widgets';

// Create a plain iframe
const iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
iframe.src = 'https://your-trusted-origin.com';
iframe.style.width = '100%';
iframe.style.height = '100vh';
iframe.setAttribute('referrerpolicy', 'no-referrer'); // Adjust as needed

// Wrap in a Lumino widget
const panel = new Widget();
panel.node.appendChild(iframe);
```

### Choosing the Right `referrerpolicy`
| Policy                          | Behavior |
|----------------------------------|----------|
| `no-referrer`                    | No referrer sent. |
| `no-referrer-when-downgrade`      | Full referrer over HTTPS; none over HTTP. |
| `origin`                          | Only sends `https://your-jupyterlab.com`, no path. |
| `strict-origin`                   | Sends origin only, even for same-origin requests. |
| `strict-origin-when-cross-origin` *(Default)* | Full referrer on same-origin, only origin on cross-origin. |

